ications, she looks in particular at the process of self-improvement for these volunteers. The competing visions of charity Allahyari finds at these two organizations reveal the complicated and contradictory politics of caring for the poor in the United States today.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBénévolatxCas, Études dexAspect religieuxxChristianisme. 0aChurch work with the homelessxCase studiesxCaliforniaxSacramento. 0aChurch work with the homelesszCaliforniazSacramentovCase studies. 0aComportement d'aidexCas, Études dexAspect religieuxxChristianisme. 0aHelping behaviorxCase studiesxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aHelping behaviorxReligious aspectsxChristianityvCase studies. 0aMouvements sociauxxCas, Études dexCaliforniexSacramentoxCaliforniaxSacramento. 0aPastorale des sans-abrixCas, Études dexCaliforniexSacramento. 0aSocial movementsxCase studiesxCaliforniaxSacramento. 0aSocial movementszCaliforniazSacramentovCase studies. 0aVoluntarismxCase studiesxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aVoluntarismxReligious aspectsxChristianityvCase studies. 4aAnthropology. 4aCultural & Social. 4aSocial Science. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aAllahyari, Rebecca Anne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022145140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093532740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520935327423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520935327/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles